# Day 04 - Understanding the CSS Box Model

## Goal for Today

- Understand the CSS Box Model
- Learn spacing and sizing concepts
- Improve yesterday's registration page using proper layouts

## What I Learned
Focus was understanding how browsers calculate the size of every HTML element. I learned that every element is essentially a box consisting of:

- Content
- Padding
- Border
- Margin

I also explored:

- `display` property
- `width` and `height`
- `max-width`
- `box-sizing`
- `overflow`
- Browser developer tools for inspecting element dimensions

One important concept was using `box-sizing`: `border-box`, which makes layouts much easier to manage because padding and borders are included in the elements total width and height.
